In Week 5 of Trump\'92s second term, the pattern that had been emerging snapped into clearer focus. The presidency was no longer only pushing against the edges of law and custom; it was building a parallel state beside the old one and hollowing the old one out. The Department of Government Efficiency, run by Elon Musk and his allies, moved deeper into the machinery of government. Courts, Congress, and civil society tried to respond, but their efforts were scattered and often late. The week\'92s events showed a government that still held elections and passed budgets, yet was steadily rewiring who held power, whose voices counted, and which facts would be allowed to stand. The shell remained. The wiring changed.\
