Alongside the firings came a set of executive orders that rewrote the relationship between the presidency and the rest of the state. One order told agencies to review and de\uc0\u8209 prioritize enforcement of regulations the White House deemed unconstitutional or beyond statutory authority. Another ordered the reduction or elimination of specific entities, from the Presidio Trust to the United States Institute of Peace, and the termination of advisory committees. A third brought independent regulatory agencies\'97such as the SEC and FTC\'97under direct White House and OIRA review, requiring them to submit rules and policy priorities for presidential approval. These moves did not abolish Congress or the courts. They did something subtler. They shifted day\u8209 to\u8209 day control of regulation and administration into the president\'92s hands, making it harder for independent experts to act without political clearance. Independence became a formality.\
