The same logic appeared in the spending realm. The administration implemented a nationwide freeze on federal spending, despite laws that require the president to carry out programs Congress has funded. Agencies were told to halt or slow disbursements, including for EV subsidies and CHIPS Act projects. Disaster aid was treated as discretionary leverage: Georgia\'92s request for more time to apply for hurricane assistance was denied, even as other states watched. These acts turned the power of the purse into a bargaining chip. They signaled that appropriations would be honored or withheld not only on fiscal grounds, but also on political ones. Money followed favor.\
